 After two years of mainstream I could see he wasnt making progress and the school were really not meeting his educational or emotional needs. &#10;He now goes to SNS and is doing brilliantly. I feel like a different person, like a weight has been lifted from my shoulders. His school goes right through to 16 so I dont have to worry about transition until then. I just feel he is 'safe' where he is. &#10;Its a very personal decision and I know its a tough one.&#10;The more information you have about what is available in your area the better.&#10;Hope it all works out for you and your boy"/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="875" language="en" documentId="4975" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Becki J" date="28-06-11 21:51" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://www.netmums.com/coffeehouse/advice-support-40/special-needs-disabilities-support-502/598821-mainstream-special-needs-school-all.html" topic="mainstreaming" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="4975" notes="" title="Mainstream or Special Needs School?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="57"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="58" end="146"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="147" end="442"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="443" end="696"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="55" sofa="1" begin="697" end="753"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="59" sofa="1" begin="754" end="832"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="63" sofa="1" begin="833" end="875"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51 55 59 63"/></xmi:XMI>